The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Jalandhar, April 1 (PTI): A US-based man from Punjab, who posed as a senior police officer and travelled in a car fitted with a beacon on his trips to India, was arrested yesterday.          
	A fake identity card, a superintendents uniform, stamps of senior police officers, a few SIM cards and mobile phones were recovered from Balwinder Singh. A Jalandhar superintendent of police said a case had been registered against Singh who had also posed as a businessman and taken money from some people earlier.                   
	Jammu (PTI): A policeman was arrested on Tuesday after 108 rounds of AK-rifle ammunition were found on him. Acting on a tip-off, police raided the house of havaldar Abdul Gani in the Basholi area and found the ammunition.                  
	Visakhapatnam (PTI): Three workers died from suffocation when they fell into a tank at the Hindustan Petroleum Corporation unit here on Monday. The mishap occurred while they were repairing the oil tank.                  
	Varanasi (PTI): A French couple stripped at the Ganga riverfront, allegedly under the influence of drugs, and later managed to escape from hospital where they had been brought by police. The scene took place when people tried to help the semi-conscious couple.                  
	Jaipur (PTI): A woman killed herself and her daughter in Rainwal village, 95km from here, by jumping into a well on Monday night, police said. Apparently family disputes drove her to death.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): Police came to know of an illegal trade in arms and ammunition following the arrest of a six-member gang here, an official said on Tuesday. The racket came to light during interrogation of the gang. The six, held in connection with a murder, told the police they were purchasing country-made revolvers and ammunition from Meerut, Uttar Pradesh, city police commissioner N. Achutha Rao said.
                                                                                                                           
